Today is expected to be the last day Hawks senior investigator Kobus Roelofse appears before the State Capture Inquiry. JOHANNESBURG - Friday is expected to be the last day Hawks senior investigator Kobus Roelofse appears before the State Capture Inquiry after three days in the hot seat. READ: Crime intelligence's piggy bank detailed at Zondo Commission On Thursday he told the inquiry that some top brass in the SAPS and the NPA  tried to shield former crime intelligence boss Richard Mdluli from prosecution His testimony continues on Friday.